HEADWORD: Eikosylene
<hw>Ei*kos"y*lene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>e'i`kosi</grk> twenty + acet<ets>ylene</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A liquid hydrocarbon, <chform>C20H38</chform>,
of the acetylene series, obtained from brown coal.</def>⟦br⟧
